---

BACKGROUND — understand this first before writing code:

We have two ways incidents get created in Remedy:

WAY 1 — AUTOMATION TOOL:
Our internal automation tool hits the Remedy API 
directly using a service account to create incidents.
The service account credentials are stored in our 
config (the exact key you found in Investigation 1).
When this happens Remedy automatically stores that 
service account name as the Submitter on the incident.
Our automation tool also always sets:
  - ReportingSource = "automation"
  - Notes field always contains "Incident details" text

WAY 2 — FRONTDOOR:
Users manually go to the FrontDoor portal, fill a form,
submit a request, get a REQ number, copy it into Remedy
and create the incident manually.
The Submitter in this case is the individual user's 
account name, NOT our service account.
Users CAN manually change ReportingSource to "automation"
in Remedy — so ReportingSource alone is not reliable 
enough to classify an incident as automation tool.

---

THE CORRECT CLASSIFICATION LOGIC:

An incident is AUTOMATION TOOL if any of these 
two paths are true:

PATH 1 — Submitter matches service account (strongest signal):
  incident.Submitter == service account name from config
  (case-insensitive)
  → If TRUE: immediately automation tool, stop checking
  → This cannot be faked by a regular user because 
    it is set by the API authentication, not manually

PATH 2 — All three conditions together (fallback):
  Only check this path if PATH 1 failed
  Condition A: ReportingSource == "automation" (case-insensitive)
  Condition B: Notes contains "Incident details" (case-insensitive)
  → If BOTH A and B are true: automation tool
  → If either A or B is false: frontdoor

EVERYTHING ELSE = FRONTDOOR

---

VISUALIZED AS A DECISION TREE:

Submitter = service account?
        │
       YES ──────────────────────→ ✅ AUTOMATION TOOL
        │
        NO
        │
        ▼
ReportingSource = "automation"?
        │
        NO ───────────────────────→ ❌ FRONTDOOR
        │
       YES
        │
        ▼
Notes contains "Incident details"?
        │
       YES ──────────────────────→ ✅ AUTOMATION TOOL
        │
        NO ───────────────────────→ ❌ FRONTDOOR

---

