Inject IConfiguration into IncidentUsageService 
if not already injected.

Read the service account name using the EXACT config 
key you found in Investigation 1.

private string GetServiceAccountName()
{
    return _configuration["EXACT_KEY_FROM_INVESTIGATION_1"];
    // Use the real key you found
    // e.g. _configuration["Remedy:Username"]
    // NEVER hardcode the actual account name here
    // The config already has different values for 
    // nonprod and prod environments automatically
}

This means:
- Nonprod config has nonprod service account → used automatically
- Prod config has prod service account → used automatically
- No environment checks needed in the code
- If account name ever changes, only config needs updating

