FIX 4 — Apply the method in ALL 3 places inside GetUsageStats():

This is critical — the SAME method must be used 
everywhere. No inline logic. No duplicate conditions.

PLACE 1 — Total counts:
var automationCount = allRemedyIncidents
    .Count(i => IsAutomationToolIncident(i));
var frontDoorCount = 
    allRemedyIncidents.Count - automationCount;

PLACE 2 — Trend grouping:
When building TrendPointDto for each date/hour/week group:
new TrendPointDto
{
    Label = g.Key,
    AutomationTool = g.Count(i => 
        IsAutomationToolIncident(i)),
    FrontDoor = g.Count(i => 
        !IsAutomationToolIncident(i))
}

PLACE 3 — Incident row list:
When building each IncidentRowDto:
Source = IsAutomationToolIncident(i) 
    ? "automation_tool" 
    : "frontdoor"

